“Dean Orion gets it – better than any book or course I know – about the journey each creative person must take to produce work that is not only meaningful but commercial.”
Tom Teicholz
Writer, Producer, and award-winning Jounalist of TOMMYWOOD.
“Dean Orion brings a fresh voice to the ancient art of storytelling in his pull-no-punches primer.  He not only helps you answer the age-old question, “Am I a writer?” but as a screenwriter, Disney Imagineer and interactivity expert extraordinaire he also helps you clear the hurdles of writing as a professional – an art in and of itself.”
Maria Alexander
Author and Interactive Designer
“If you’re smart enough to read LIVE TO WRITE ANOTHER DAY, Dean Orion will tell you that “writing is in his DNA.” And from my own professional experiences working with him, I know that to be very true.  Few working writers possess Dean’s ability to offer such open and honest insight into the dream-to-deadline reality of what it means to call yourself a scribe.  Luckily for all of us, he’s also chosen to share his adventures here. So make the journey a little easier on yourself. Read Dean Orion’s story and I promise you’ll have a much better time writing your own.”
Trey Callaway
Co-Executive Producer, CSI:NY, Professor, USC School of Cinematic Arts
“I found this book inspiring as a writer and as an executive.  Dean offers many valuable words of wisdom and gives us full insight into the process that he has developed over the his many years in the business, with concise, applicable tools that cross multiple disciplines.  After reading this book I immediately applied some of his tactics in my everyday life, and I am so grateful for the time it has saved me!  If you want a great process for cultivating inspiration to let the story flow out of you (instead of dragging it out as I typically did) then this is the book for you.”
Sybil Grieb
Author of BRILLIANCE AND ACCIDENTS, Publisher of SUBTEXT literary magazine, and Online Advertising Executive 
“If writing is 90% perspiration, then nobody knows how to sweat it out better than Dean Orion.   I’ve never met a more disciplined writer in my life.  If anyone knows how to Live To Write Another Day, it’s him.  And if you want to learn to do the same then this is the book for you.”
Karey Kirkpatrick
Screenwriter, CHICKEN RUN, Writer/Director, OVER THE HEDGE
